                <note rend="inline" type="source">651.116 Nitrate/40: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in France</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Shaw</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-11-25T19:00:00+00:00"
                            >November 25, 1931—7 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received November 25—3 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>802. Embassy’s 785, November 23, 5 p.m. On yesterday afternoon the
                    representatives of the American and Chilean nitrate interests informed the
                    Minister of Agriculture that they declined to pay contribution, whereupon they
                    were told by him that they would receive no import licenses. The Embassy has
                    confirmed at the Foreign Office that the above is the attitude of the Ministry
                    of Agriculture. Although not present at the meeting, it is reported that the
                    Norwegians understand that they also are to receive no licenses. The Embassy is
                    still working informally upon the matter.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Shaw</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
